<TITLE> HC to hear Jamuna petition against Future Park demolition Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 19 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court will hear on Thursday a petition against a Rajuk order for demolishing unapproved portions of Jamuna Future Park. The HC has also ordered not to pull down any illegal construction until the hearing is held. A bench of justice AHM Shamsuddin Chowdhury and justice Md Borhanuddin passed the order on Tuesday. Rajdhani Unnayan Kortripakkhothe city development agencyon Sunday asked the authorities to knock down the illegal portions of Jamuna Future Park, a project of Jamuna Group, within seven days. Rajuk official Shaqur Rahman had told bdnews24.com that Jamuna Future Park had been given permission to build up to six floors, but they built higher breaching the approval. Nurul Islam, chief of Jamuna Future Park and owner of the daily Jugantar newspaper filed a petition against the Rajuk order. The much-vaunted Future Park is being constructed on 10 acres of land in the capital's Bashundhara area. Jamuna has been claiming that it would be the largest shopping mall in South Asia. 
